                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/540a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-28T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 28, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>205. I discussed briefly with the President today action to be taken with respect
                    to Soviet note of August 27. He is not in favor of writing another note to the
                    Soviet Government but thinks that a succinct statement setting forth position of
                    this Government should be issued by me. Such a statement is now being prepared
                    in the Department and will be submitted to the President for his approval
                    tomorrow. He seems to feel that the action suggested by you, such as the
                    withdrawal of the exequaturs of the Soviet consuls in the United States, should
                    be held in reserve. Please give any information you deem pertinent, and do not
                    hesitate to express your opinion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
